    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 9200 9300 9400 MODELS BUILT AFTER JANUARY 1, 1995 - INSTRUMENTS
        (New Data Link Driven Instrument Cluster) - DESCRIPTION - AMMETER (OPTIONAL)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>AMMETER (OPTIONAL)</title>
        <para>An optional ammeter (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0815512">Figure 12</hotlnk>) is available to display the current flow between the vehicle's
            batteries and the vehicle's loads and alternator (less the cranking motor). Thus, the ammeter will display a
            positive reading when the alternator is charging the batteries, and it will display a negative reading when
            the alternator is supplying less current than the vehicle is drawing.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0815512" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0815512" filename="../figg08/G0815512.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Ammeter</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
